title: This is Your City Rally
description:
We‚Äôre less than three months away from the August primary. I‚Äôve run a lot of campaigns over the years, and I know how important it is to set ambitious but achievable goals. So I‚Äôm calling it now. Here‚Äôs what we‚Äôre going to do, together:

We‚Äôre going to be in first place on August 5th.

That‚Äôs right, you heard it. We‚Äôre not just going to make it through the primary. We‚Äôre going to win more votes than Bruce Harrell.

We can absolutely do this. But it‚Äôs not going to happen automatically, and it‚Äôs not going to be easy. That said, there is one easy thing you can do right now to help us achieve this goal:

RSVP for the This Is Your City Rally coming up on Saturday, May 31st. [link]

This rally will kick off an intense, all-hands-on-deck, ten-week stretch of bringing our message to voters ‚Äî especially infrequent and new voters ‚Äî across Seattle. Because THAT is how we‚Äôre going to win first place in the primary: by talking face-to-face with tens of thousands of people who aren‚Äôt going to vote this year unless we reach them.

Needless to say, I‚Äôm going to need your help, whether that‚Äôs knocking on doors, phonebanking, talking to people at festivals and light rail stations, writing letters to fellow tenants in your apartment building, or texting your friends and family. You can do a lot of that right now, of course ‚Äî but we‚Äôre all going to have to turn it up a notch in the final stretch.

But beyond all that, here are three reasons why I‚Äôm really hoping to see you on May 31st:

To show our strength. Our rally will send a clear message to all the people who still think Harrell has this race locked down. At our March kickoff, 150 people came together to launch this campaign. Let‚Äôs demonstrate how much our numbers have grown!

To build for the long haul. I know we can win this race, but it‚Äôs about much more than getting one person elected. When I‚Äôm in City Hall, it‚Äôs not like the entrenched interests that are fighting us on the campaign trail are going to give up and say ‚ÄúHow can we help?‚Äù They‚Äôre going to keep fighting us. They‚Äôre going to try to make sure I‚Äôm not able to do any of the good things we want to see happen for Seattle, and they‚Äôre going to try to turn the public against us. We‚Äôre going to need a powerful movement of people on the outside, organizing and building power, so we can make progress. Building that movement starts now.

Oh yeah, and it‚Äôs going to be fun! Great company, good food, rousing speeches (but not too many), and meaningful action. I‚Äôm not saying there will be cornhole, but I‚Äôm also not saying there won‚Äôt be. What better way to spend a couple hours on your Saturday? 

Location and time are TBD, but it will be transit accessible. It will help us plan if you RSVP now!

title: Freedom Fridays: THE EMOLUMENTS CLAUSE
description:

The Emoluments Clause of the U.S. Constitution, Article I, Section 9, Clause 8:

In other words, it restricts federal officials from accepting gifts, titles, or emoluments from foreign governments without Congressional consent. Its primary purpose is to prevent foreign influence and corruption of U.S. officials.

The ultimate Trump grift = accepting a $400 million Boeing 747-8 jumbo jet, a Flying Palace, from the Qatari royal family.
We know Trump can't be bothered to read the Constitution or understand the oath he took to the Office of the Presidency, and if MAGA Republican lawmakers allow this grift, it tells us what they think of the Constitution.
